* Best Song Written for Visual Media: "[[Safe & Sound (Taylor Swift song)|Safe & Sound]]" (2012)<ref name="GrammyTB">{{cite web|title=T Bone Burnett|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/t-bone-burnett|website=GRAMMY.com|access-date=July 16, 2017|language=en|date=May 14, 2017}}</ref>

===Other awards===
In 2010, Burnett won several awards for the movie ''Crazy Heart''. He and [[Ryan Bingham]] shared the Academy Award for Best Original Song and the Golden Globe Award for Best Song for "[[The Weary Kind]]".<ref name="Gilbert">{{cite web|last1=Gilbert|first1=Calvin|title=Jeff Bridges, Ryan Bingham, T Bone Burnett Win Oscars for Crazy Heart|url=http://www.cmt.com/news/1633370/jeff-bridges-ryan-bingham-t-bone-burnett-win-oscars-for-crazy-heart/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150216194903/http://www.cmt.com/news/1633370/jeff-bridges-ryan-bingham-t-bone-burnett-win-oscars-for-crazy-heart/|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 16, 2015|website=CMT News|access-date=July 17, 2017|date=March 8, 2010}}</ref> The song won them a [[Critics' Choice Movie Awards|Critics' Choice Award]] and won Burnett a [[Satellite Award]] from the International Press Academy. For the score, Burnett and [[Stephen Bruton]] won an award from [[Los Angeles Film Critics Association]] and Burnett won the [[Frederick Loewe]] award. He shared the award for Best First Feature at the Independent Spirit Awards with the producers ([[Robert Duvall]], Rob Carliner and Judy Cairo) and director [[Scott Cooper (director)|Scott Cooper]].{{citation needed|date=July 2017}} He was awarded an honorary doctorate in performing arts from the [[University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill]] in May 2019.<ref name="T Bone Burnett : Commencement: The University of North Carolina">{{cite web|last1=University Communications|title=T Bone Burnett : Commencement: The University of North Carolina|url=https://commencement.unc.edu/2019/03/18/t-bone-burnett/|website= UNC Commencement|access-date=May 12, 2019|date=May 18, 2019}}</ref>

